HEADWORD: Wheft
<hw>Wheft</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>See <er>Waft</er>, <pos>n.</pos>, 4.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>A kind of streamer or flag used
either as a signal, or at the masthead for ornament or to indicate the
direction of the wind to aid in steering.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Whelk</ent>⟦br⟧
